Data Refresh 10

In this step we are going to work on data refresh on the canvas, that actually refresh the whole model.

Steps for to create the table

1. First let go to power query editor under transform data, then click on New source then blank query.

2. Then we write the query = DateTime.LocalNow().

3. Rename our table - Data Refresh and convert it to a table.

4. Then we will see a new column, rename it to Date time and duplicate the actual column it self , rename it Date, change the              format to date/ date only.

5. Then we duplicate the new column i.e Date time and rename it Time, then we go to time in the tool bar and change the                    format  to time/ time only.

N.B. The data refresh does not change if we try to refresh individual table, instead works when we want to refresh the whole                  model. The key is Data refresh table has to refresh.


Steps for this report

Go to our report page to work on our card for data refresh.

1. Drag and drop card from visualization.

2. Drag and drop Date Time column from Data Refresh table.

3. Add a title text and use same format through out the dashboard. (Refer step 4)

4. Customize Data label

  •     Color - white
  •     Display units auto
  •     Text size - 15pt
  •     Font family - Arial

5. Category - off

6.  Boarder - on

  • Color - white 30% darker
